1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
I knew with two pretty good blows to the back of the head that it didn't release, that I

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:09,000
was probably going to have to do something a little more drastic.

3
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:24,000
About a quarter mile into that run, I ended up hearing some pine needle

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:31,000
rustle, like a stick break, and I turned around and just was pretty bummed out

5
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
to see an outline chasing after me.

6
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
It just kind of kept running and lunged at me.

7
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:47,000
It was going toward my face, so I threw up my hands to kind of block my face.

8
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
At which point, it grabbed onto my hand and wrist,

9
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:58,000
and from there, it started to claw at my face and neck,

10
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:03,000
and that's when kind of my fear response turned into more of a fight response.

11
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:07,000
There was a point where I was concerned that I wasn't going to make it out of it,

12
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:13,000
and I think it might have been a mix of me tussling with the cat and it's so clawing at me,

13
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
and then thinking about another cat potentially coming along.

14
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:22,000
It got a claw on my lip, and I tried to throw it off me at that point,

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,000
and then you took a little tumble down the south side of the trail,

16
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:32,000
and down there just kind of had a little wrestling match at which point I was able to get on top of it,

17
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:41,000
pin its back legs, so it didn't get any soft tissue scratched out in my other regions.

18
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,000
I was grabbing around for sticks.

19
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:48,000
I only had my left hand free, my right hand was still walking its jaws.

20
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:55,000
I tried to get out of its neck to see if I could stab it in the neck to get it to release.

21
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:03,000
That wasn't working the sticks were breaking, so then I picked up a rock that I had seen kind of near us.

22
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
It was pretty heavy, it was kind of hard to reel,

23
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:12,000
and I tried to give it a few bashes in the back of the head,

24
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:20,000
but unfortunately I just kind of had tough times swinging it with my arms still locked into the cat's jaws.

25
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:25,000
I stepped on it on its neck with my right foot,

26
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:32,000
and just slowly after a few minutes I thought it would be getting close,

27
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:40,000
and then it started thrashing again and had a few more scratches that resulted from those thrashes at that point.

28
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:47,000
And I'd say another couple minutes later it finally stopped moving and then jaws opened,

29
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:52,000
and I was able to kind of scramble back up the hill and get the heck out of dodge.

30
00:02:52,000 --> 00:03:00,000
And I guess in my mind I replayed it. It seems like a long time, but I've been thinking 10 minutes at most.

31
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:09,000
He did all the right things, he put his hands up and yelled at it, and it still came after him.

